ld note that my guild does not practice your crime.  Items are rolled on by those who can use them most.  The only way any item ever rolls to sell instead of wear is if there is NOBODY in the guild who will wear it.  Even then, it would go in the guild bank before it's given up to sell.  Also, the old argument about which priest class can roll on an item is settled simply as follows:  Who needs it?  Will they definitely wear it?  Does that person need it more than this person?  Why?  Now roll!  Be fair to ALL your members, NOT just tanks and clerics.  BTW yes, Shamans can slow, so they usually are ahead of druids in loot order.  Keep in mind that, as far as magic goes, a druid can do ANYTHING, at least in some degree.  The purpose of the druid class in a raid is to fill in wherever things seem weakest.  If I were in a guild and saw someone get scrood on a raid like many of you do to druids, I would port, target myself, and /guildremove, without a single word.  Luckily, I won't ever have to do that because I was lucky enough to find a player organization that actually has values other than making the same three people more powerfull constantly.<br><br>Baron Galiem Vaelant<br>Tunare's Wanderer of 51 Seasons<br>&lt;Honor Elite&gt;<br>The Seventh Hammer<br><br><em id=fs8>Edited, Mon Feb 10 10:19:54 2003</em></p>&nbsp;<br>--Pay attention to the cracked streets and the broken homes.. Some call it slums, some call it nice! I wanna take you to a wasteland I like to call my home.. Welcome to paradise!</td></td></tr>
